00:10:46.950 --> 00:10:49.530
So that's when you go down that VQ arm.

261
00:10:49.530 --> 00:10:51.480
If it's a traditional lower dose

262
00:10:51.480 --> 00:10:55.710
that we have now, CTPA is is totally fine according to ACOG.

263
00:10:55.710 --> 00:10:58.353
So they should specify that for you on the boards.

264
00:10:59.970 --> 00:11:01.320
If a VQ is done

265
00:11:01.320 --> 00:11:05.100
and shows a high probability of having a PE, do you need

266
00:11:05.100 --> 00:11:07.530
to confirm this with the CTPA?

267
00:11:07.530 --> 00:11:10.050
It depends on your pretest probability.

268
00:11:10.050 --> 00:11:12.300
So if you had high pretest probability

269
00:11:12.300 --> 00:11:15.030
and your VQ is high, you're done.

270
00:11:15.030 --> 00:11:15.863
That's a PE.

271
00:11:15.863 --> 00:11:18.360
You don't need to confirm it any other way.

272
00:11:18.360 --> 00:11:20.730
If you had a low pretest probability

273
00:11:20.730 --> 00:11:23.880
and a low risk VQ, you're done.

274
00:11:23.880 --> 00:11:25.890
You've ruled it out.

275
00:11:25.890 --> 00:11:29.160
If you have a completely normal VQ, you're done.

276
00:11:29.160 --> 00:11:32.640
You've ruled it out regardless of your pretest probability.

277
00:11:32.640 --> 00:11:35.610
Any other combination, you need to confirm it.

278
00:11:35.610 --> 00:11:37.883
Okay, so I think that person was asking if it was high

279
00:11:37.883 --> 00:11:40.860
pretest and high test chance on the VQ.

280
00:11:40.860 --> 00:11:41.693
Yep, you're done.

281
00:11:41.693 --> 00:11:42.993
Don't get that CTPA.

282
00:11:45.390 --> 00:11:46.830
<v ->Okay, tons of questions David.</v>

283
00:11:46.830 --> 00:11:48.600
We're gonna try to get through 'em as best as we can.

284
00:11:48.600 --> 00:11:49.433
So with COPD,

285
00:11:50.460 --> 00:11:51.720
a lot of you like this question,

286
00:11:51.720 --> 00:11:52.770
what dose of Augmentin?

287
00:11:52.770 --> 00:11:56.220
I like 875 twice a day for five days.

288
00:11:56.220 --> 00:11:58.530
But that's dependent of course on a normal

