300
00:12:37.350 --> 00:12:39.540
Lots of questions about the eosinophil count.

301
00:12:39.540 --> 00:12:40.740
Why are we doing this?

302
00:12:40.740 --> 00:12:43.020
Well, the eosinophil count,

303
00:12:43.020 --> 00:12:44.760
remember we were taught in medical school,

304
00:12:44.760 --> 00:12:46.380
that in a high eosinophil,

305
00:12:46.380 --> 00:12:48.420
if I just see this on a routine CBC,

306
00:12:48.420 --> 00:12:49.950
I typically think of two things, right?

307
00:12:49.950 --> 00:12:50.783
What are they?

308
00:12:52.230 --> 00:12:53.980
Allergies and what's the other one?

309
00:12:55.140 --> 00:12:56.523
Parasitic infections.

310
00:12:58.110 --> 00:12:59.220
At the end of the day,

311
00:12:59.220 --> 00:13:03.090
eosinophil counts indicate inflammation.

312
00:13:03.090 --> 00:13:08.090
So if they have higher inflammation based on that count,

313
00:13:08.250 --> 00:13:09.780
they're therefore more likely to respond

314
00:13:09.780 --> 00:13:11.490
to an anti-inflammatory.

315
00:13:11.490 --> 00:13:12.900
Does that make sense?

316
00:13:12.900 --> 00:13:15.060
Now these are the guidelines folks.

317
00:13:15.060 --> 00:13:16.950
This is the boards here.

318
00:13:16.950 --> 00:13:20.280
What you do in clinical practice sometimes

319
00:13:20.280 --> 00:13:22.200
might be a little different.

320
00:13:22.200 --> 00:13:24.720
Again, questions about decreasing exacerbations,

321
00:13:24.720 --> 00:13:26.730
hospitalizations and mortality.

322
00:13:26.730 --> 00:13:29.280
The only thing that improves their lifestyle,

323
00:13:29.280 --> 00:13:32.550
their longevity is what?

324
00:13:32.550 --> 00:13:33.420
Quitting smoking.

325
00:13:33.420 --> 00:13:34.890
It's the only thing.

326
00:13:34.890 --> 00:13:37.140
Only thing that keeps 'em alive longer.

327
00:13:37.140 --> 00:13:38.430
Everything else is symptomatic.

328
00:13:38.430 --> 00:13:40.350
Reducing exacerbations

329
00:13:40.350 --> 00:13:44.130
and hospitalizations are your inhaled corticosteroids,

330
00:13:44.130 --> 00:13:45.570
your azithromycin,

331
00:13:45.570 --> 00:13:48.810
and then your roflumilast in your patients at

332
00:13:48.810 --> 00:13:50.943
higher levels of GOLD three to four.

333
00:13:52.590 --> 00:13:54.123
Okay, let's see.

334
00:13:55.350 --> 00:13:57.240
Oh yeah, here's a good one, David.

335
00:13:57.240 --> 00:13:59.100
Question about using azithromycin

336
00:13:59.100 --> 00:14:01.080
for your exacerbations in COPD

337
00:14:01.080 --> 00:14:03.240
because of the anti-inflammatory properties.

338
00:14:03.240 --> 00:14:07.260
Yes, but azithromycin has fallen out

339
00:14:07.260 --> 00:14:09.540
