00:15:49.440 --> 00:15:53.130
do they have like a lifetime risk of high risk of clot?

381
00:15:53.130 --> 00:15:54.720
The answer is no.

382
00:15:54.720 --> 00:15:56.670
Wells' criteria really says if you've had

383
00:15:56.670 --> 00:15:59.130
that treatment within the last six months,

384
00:15:59.130 --> 00:16:01.710
so if you're no longer being treated for your cancer

385
00:16:01.710 --> 00:16:03.930
and you're considered to be a cancer survivor,

386
00:16:03.930 --> 00:16:06.870
you would not get those points on that Wells' criteria.

387
00:16:06.870 --> 00:16:09.840
So six months of treatment and then

388
00:16:09.840 --> 00:16:11.640
because you said 40% of people

389
00:16:11.640 --> 00:16:13.980
with a proximal DBT also have a PE,

390
00:16:13.980 --> 00:16:16.830
should we be scanning all of them with CTPAs?

