00:16:16.830 --> 00:16:19.380
No, it's not gonna change your management.

392
00:16:19.380 --> 00:16:21.990
If you've already determined that they have a DBT

393
00:16:21.990 --> 00:16:23.430
that you're gonna be treating,

394
00:16:23.430 --> 00:16:26.010
doesn't really change anything if they have a PE.

395
00:16:26.010 --> 00:16:27.720
Now symptomatically, if they're struggling

396
00:16:27.720 --> 00:16:29.820
or they're hypoxic, there could be other things you need

397
00:16:29.820 --> 00:16:31.140
to get that test for.

398
00:16:31.140 --> 00:16:32.760
But just for routine screening

399
00:16:32.760 --> 00:16:35.190
for asymptomatic, from a respiratory standpoint,

400
00:16:35.190 --> 00:16:37.590
there's no reason to get a CTPA if you've

401
00:16:37.590 --> 00:16:39.213
diagnosed a DBT.

