00:19:04.560 --> 00:19:08.400
for spacers in today's world.

461
00:19:08.400 --> 00:19:10.890
And then the biggest one,

462
00:19:10.890 --> 00:19:12.750
tons of different questions asked in lots

463
00:19:12.750 --> 00:19:15.270
of different ways about this new SMART therapy.

464
00:19:15.270 --> 00:19:17.610
I really want you all to know this.

465
00:19:17.610 --> 00:19:19.980
So this is single maintenance and reliever therapy.

466
00:19:19.980 --> 00:19:24.270
Single means we only need to prescribe one inhaler.

467
00:19:24.270 --> 00:19:28.320
The patient uses this inhaler as needed

468
00:19:28.320 --> 00:19:30.360
and they step it up as needed.

469
00:19:30.360 --> 00:19:31.770
So if my asthma,

470
00:19:31.770 --> 00:19:35.040
like I have mild intermittent asthma, right now I'm good.

471
00:19:35.040 --> 00:19:36.930
I'm not using my inhaler.

472
00:19:36.930 --> 00:19:41.550
If my asthma starts acting up, I start using it twice a day,

473
00:19:41.550 --> 00:19:43.443
maybe up to four times a day,

474
00:19:44.400 --> 00:19:46.410
as needed to control my symptoms.

475
00:19:46.410 --> 00:19:48.810
And then I step down and up as necessary.

476
00:19:48.810 --> 00:19:52.200
You do not need to prescribe a short-acting beta

477
00:19:52.200 --> 00:19:53.670
agonist with this.

478
00:19:53.670 --> 00:19:56.580
Remember for formoterol is unique

479
00:19:56.580 --> 00:19:58.260
among long-acting beta agonist

480
00:19:58.260 --> 00:20:00.450
'cause it works less than five minutes

481
00:20:00.450 --> 00:20:02.880
and it has high lipophilicity.

482
00:20:02.880 --> 00:20:05.910
So it penetrates the lung tissues very quickly.

483
00:20:05.910 --> 00:20:07.410
So it's the real star of the show.

484
00:20:07.410 --> 00:20:09.480
Now you got two options.

485
00:20:09.480 --> 00:20:12.960
You've got in the clinical studies, the sigma trials,

486
00:20:12.960 --> 00:20:17.550
they used budesonide with formoterol

487
00:20:17.550 --> 00:20:20.940
and the name of that inhaler is Symbicort,

488
00:20:20.940 --> 00:20:23.580
available branded or generic.

489
00:20:23.580 --> 00:20:28.320
We also have formoterol in combination

490
00:20:28.320 --> 00:20:30.480
with mometasone,

491
00:20:30.480 --> 00:20:33.120
which is a different inhaled corticosteroid.

492
00:20:33.120 --> 00:20:37.083
The branded name product there is Dulera.

493
00:20:37.950 --> 00:20:42.950
Most allergists and pulmonologists endorse using either one

494
00:20:43.320 --> 00:20:46.170
because again, the star of the show here

495
00:20:46.170 --> 00:20:48.660
with SMART therapy is formoterol.

496
00:20:48.660 --> 00:20:52.710
Not the specific nuances of which inhaled corticosteroid.

497
00:20:52.710 --> 00:20:56.520
And there are nuances, but that's a topic for another day.

498
00:20:56.520 --> 00:20:58.980
<v ->I cannot emphasize this enough</v>

499
00:20:58.980 --> 00:21:01.950
that there will most likely be a question on the exam

500
00:21:01.950 --> 00:21:04.170
related to this SMART therapy.

501
00:21:04.170 --> 00:21:06.360
This is where we have moved.

502
00:21:06.360 --> 00:21:09.120
I think in the next, hopefully won't take a decade,

503
00:21:09.120 --> 00:21:11.430
but I think in the next decade this is gonna be

504
00:21:11.430 --> 00:21:12.900
just like what we experience now.

505
00:21:12.900 --> 00:21:15.270
When the patient comes in and says they have asthma

506
00:21:15.270 --> 00:21:17.880
and they've never heard of an inhaled corticosteroid,

507
00:21:17.880 --> 00:21:19.860
I question the diagnosis

508
00:21:19.860 --> 00:21:23.280
because I'm like, how can you have this chronic disease

509
00:21:23.280 --> 00:21:25.770
and have not been on an inhaled corticosteroid?

510
00:21:25.770 --> 00:21:27.660
So then I'm like, have you ever had PFTs?

511
00:21:27.660 --> 00:21:28.493
Et cetera, et cetera.

512
00:21:28.493 --> 00:21:29.580
I think in the next three

513
00:21:29.580 --> 00:21:31.530
to five years it's gonna be the same there.

514
00:21:31.530 --> 00:21:34.470
How could you have not been on SMART therapy if you

515
00:21:34.470 --> 00:21:35.730
really have asthma?

516
00:21:35.730 --> 00:21:38.100
Okay, so I'm always calling into question,

517
00:21:38.100 --> 00:21:41.130
did we have the right diagnosis in order

518
00:21:41.130 --> 00:21:44.160
and we can only treat appropriately if we have the

519
00:21:44.160 --> 00:21:45.960
correct diagnosis.

520
00:21:45.960 --> 00:21:47.529
As you know, that's not surprising.

521
00:21:47.529 --> 00:21:49.980
<v ->And I'll say if SMART therapy was new for you guys,</v>

522
00:21:49.980 --> 00:21:52.230
it's also new for, just this month alone,

523
00:21:52.230 --> 00:21:54.300
I've put two kids on SMART therapy.

