00:23:41.423 --> 00:23:42.256
<v ->Of course not.</v>

573
00:23:42.256 --> 00:23:44.880
No, there's a question on anti-epileptic

574
00:23:44.880 --> 00:23:46.380
drug level monitoring.

575
00:23:46.380 --> 00:23:48.030
Everyone doesn't need monitoring.

576
00:23:48.030 --> 00:23:49.170
So pregnant people do,

577
00:23:49.170 --> 00:23:50.700
if they're having breakthrough seizures,

578
00:23:50.700 --> 00:23:52.260
you could do monitoring.

579
00:23:52.260 --> 00:23:54.210
CKD patients need some monitoring

580
00:23:54.210 --> 00:23:55.680
or if they're having a lot of side effects

581
00:23:55.680 --> 00:23:57.780
and you're looking for toxicity.

582
00:23:57.780 --> 00:23:59.700
If the level is high

583
00:23:59.700 --> 00:24:02.070
like appropriate and they're still having seizures,

584
00:24:02.070 --> 00:24:04.290
you need to change the agent, okay?

585
00:24:04.290 --> 00:24:06.120
If you've already changed the agent twice

586
00:24:06.120 --> 00:24:07.230
and they're still having seizures,

587
00:24:07.230 --> 00:24:09.870
think about a combo agent for those ones.

588
00:24:09.870 --> 00:24:13.290
And I would say my next most important question is,

589
00:24:13.290 --> 00:24:15.570
can you come off of anti-epileptic drugs?

590
00:24:15.570 --> 00:24:16.410
The answer is yes.

591
00:24:16.410 --> 00:24:18.480
So if you've been seizure free for two years,

592
00:24:18.480 --> 00:24:20.310
whether it's a kid or an adult,

593
00:24:20.310 --> 00:24:22.650
that's a conversation to talk about do you wanna come off

594
00:24:22.650 --> 00:24:23.670
of these meds?

595
00:24:23.670 --> 00:24:26.100
You do wanna watch out for high risk situations,

596
00:24:26.100 --> 00:24:29.700
like if it's someone who drives a big dump truck, ah,

597
00:24:29.700 --> 00:24:30.990
I'm probably gonna keep you on that.

598
00:24:30.990 --> 00:24:33.510
'Cause if you have an accidental seizure,

599
00:24:33.510 --> 00:24:35.910
that could really be life threatening for you.

600
00:24:35.910 --> 00:24:37.650
Or if you have a lot of nocturnal seizures,

601
00:24:37.650 --> 00:24:39.090
high risk of death from those.

602
00:24:39.090 --> 00:24:41.850
So even if it's been two years, I might keep you on.

603
00:24:41.850 --> 00:24:44.010
But for the average person at two years out,

604
00:24:44.010 --> 00:24:46.263
you could think about stopping those meds.

605
00:24:48.480 --> 00:24:49.890
<v ->Thank you Theresa.</v>

606
00:24:49.890 --> 00:24:51.360
Alright, so my top two I guess would be,

607
00:24:51.360 --> 00:24:53.700
there's a ton of questions and they're all answered.

608
00:24:53.700 --> 00:24:58.700
One good one was, what would be the exceptions to

609
00:24:59.220 --> 00:25:02.940
the guideline about not repeating the chest x-ray

610
00:25:02.940 --> 00:25:05.580
after treated community acquired pneumonia.

611
00:25:05.580 --> 00:25:09.060
Really if the patient doesn't respond clinically,

612
00:25:09.060 --> 00:25:11.880
then you would do further investigations.

613
00:25:11.880 --> 00:25:14.430
That guideline is for the patient that's diagnosed

614
00:25:14.430 --> 00:25:17.130
with community acquired pneumonia, they improve.

615
00:25:17.130 --> 00:25:18.150
There's no reason

616
00:25:18.150 --> 00:25:22.383
to do a follow-up chest x-ray in the patient who improves.

617
00:25:23.250 --> 00:25:28.250
And then next some good questions about why

618
00:25:28.440 --> 00:25:31.527
are we treating influenza and RSV,

619
00:25:31.527 --> 00:25:34.050
why are we testing for them and so forth?

620
00:25:34.050 --> 00:25:35.760
Why are we doing vaccines?

621
00:25:35.760 --> 00:25:38.970
A lot of it is to protect the public at large,

622
00:25:38.970 --> 00:25:41.910
even if the individual patient might be at low risk.

623
00:25:41.910 --> 00:25:46.110
This is a population based strategy, global immunizations.

624
00:25:46.110 --> 00:25:48.910
So it's very important that we try to immunize everyone.

625
00:25:49.800 --> 00:25:51.240
And then I guess lastly David,

626
00:25:51.240 --> 00:25:53.790
I would say there's 101 questions about the

627
00:25:53.790 --> 00:25:56.190
pneumococcal vaccine recommendation.

628
00:25:56.190 --> 00:25:59.250
Everything you need to know are on those slide sets.

629
00:25:59.250 --> 00:26:01.409
Yeah, don't overthink it.

630
00:26:01.409 --> 00:26:04.560
All the information is there.

631
00:26:04.560 --> 00:26:05.910
The most likely thing they're going

632
00:26:05.910 --> 00:26:10.910
to ask you is doing a PCV 20 once and done.

633
00:26:11.910 --> 00:26:13.830
<v ->I think that is going to be the question.</v>

634
00:26:13.830 --> 00:26:16.290
The whole reason there is an app is

635
00:26:16.290 --> 00:26:18.300
because of this watershed period.

636
00:26:18.300 --> 00:26:20.580
When people have gotten some and not the others.

637
00:26:20.580 --> 00:26:22.560
Once that we are past that,

